Hello IT Professionals,
 
The UITS Campus Network Engineering Team would like to make you aware of the upcoming changes to the guest wifi service at IU.
 
On Thursday, October 18, a new guest wireless network service called IU Guest will go live. [1]
On Thursday, November 1, 2018, the current guest wireless service, AT&T wireless service (attwifi) will be retired from service. [2]
 
The new IU Guest network will provide a similar experience to IU’s current attwifi network and that of other guest wireless services typically found in hotels and retail businesses. To utilize IU Guest, users will first be required to agree to terms and conditions for the service, before being advanced to a confirmation page. Upon clicking the login button on the confirmation page, they will be able to access the internet. [3]
 
If a user is on IU Guest for more than twenty-four (24) hours, they will be prompted to reaffirm the terms and conditions of use to continue to access the network.
 
The Networks team would like to remind all faculty, staff and students that they should continue to use IU Secure rather than IU Guest for the following reasons:
·         IU Guest is not encrypted
·         IU Guest may be subject to less bandwidth
·         IU Guest users may not have access to some IU resources
 
Questions? Email noc@iu.edu.
 
--IT Community Partnerships on behalf of the Campus Networks Engineering Team
 
[1] Free wireless internet service for IU campus visitors: https://kb.iu.edu/d/atkx
[2] Free connections to AT&T wireless for visitors to IU: https://kb.iu.edu/d/azqb
[3] IU Homepage: https://www.indiana.edu/
